    "intro": "Interpretation moves from what Isaiah 65 says to what it means — tracing the author's intent in its original historical context and its place in the canonical argument. The movements below follow the chapter's three structural sections: divine indictment, the logic of grace-within-judgment, and the new-creation promise. Where Hebrew vocabulary sharpens an English translation, brief notes follow. Where orthodox interpreters disagree — particularly on the referent and timing of the new creation — both positions are presented fairly.",
